  "market_context": "EUR/AUD daily candle swept the previous day high at 1.62854 and closed back inside the range at 1.62666, signalling a bearish bias and a draw toward the previous day low for the following session.",
  "key_observation": "The daily candle 2 closure (sweep of prior day high and close back inside) combined with an hourly change in state of delivery through up-close candles confirmed a protected high and a bearish open-high-low-close projection.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart, identified that price swept the previous day high (1.62854) and closed back inside the range at 1.62666, forming a bearish candle 2 closure.",
    "Step 2: Established daily bias as bearish, anticipating a draw toward previous day low and an Open-High-Low-Close (bearish OHLC) profile for the next daily candle.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to the hourly time frame to seek confirmation; observed that price had closed through the series of up-close candles forming the high, confirming a change in state of delivery and a protected high.",
    "Step 4: Waited for price to rally back into the protected zone during the New York session; price swept a short-term high to the left and closed through the down-close candle that formed it.",
    "Step 5: Entered short on the close of the confirmation hourly candle with stop placed above the swept high, targeting 2R."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit the 2R take-profit target after some time in the market.",
  "lessons": "A higher time frame candle 2 closure combined with an LTF change in state of delivery at a protected swing provides a high-probability framework: HTF bias defines direction, LTF CISD confirms it, and the session sweep delivers the entry.",
